lead_paragraph: To viewers in most of the West on Saturday, the moon will look as if it is taking a bite out of the sun, and Southern Californians will be treated to a stunning ring-shaped eclipse at sunset. "For the West in general, this is going to be a very unique eclipse because it occurs at sunset," said Alan Dyer, an editor at Astronomy magazine. "That will be the visual attraction that makes this stand out as an eclipse to remember."

headline.main: Californians to Glimpse A Rare Ring-Like Eclipse
